page.title: 04O.S. Area 4243-4041
page.content: This area is a mixture of farmland and woodland, with the A64 dual carriageway trunk road running across the South East section. The woodland covers the North West section and belongs to the Bramham Estate. The trees are mainly pine, with some oak, ash and beech. The farmland is used mainly for crops, especially barley and wheat, but there are some pasture fields with cattle and sheep. The farm, known as Windsor Farm, is positioned just off the A64 in the extreme South West of the section. The farmhouse is approximately 40 years old and four people live there. The A64 runs West to East and also has the beginnings of a slip road to the A1.
